SIMPLE: serial
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Serial
<hw>Se"ri*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to a series; consisting of a series; appearing in successive
parts or numbers; <as>as, a <ex>serial</ex> work or
publication</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Classification . . . may be more or less
<xex>serial</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>H. Spencer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to rows.</def>
<rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Serial homology</b></col>. <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <cd>See
under <er>Homology</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Serial symmetry</b></col>.
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <cd>See under <er>Symmetry</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Serial</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Serial
<hw>Se"ri*al</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A publication appearing in a
series or succession of part; a tale, or other writing, published in
successive numbers of a periodical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seriality</ent>⟦br⟧
